metadata.othernotes:
Summary
-Nami is a pirate and a thief with a bounty on her head.
-She's the navigator of her crew, and has extensive knowledge on navigation, weather science and cartography. Her dream is to draw the first map of the entire world.
-The world of One Piece is segregated into different seas and islands, thus making travel quite difficult. In the present day of the story piracy is rampant throughout the world, with the most powerful pirates gathering in the Grand Line, the most dangerous sea that covers the entire world.
-Despite being pirates and being branded as criminals, Nami and her crew are more akin to adventurers, traveling aroud the world trying to fulfill their dreams.

Personality
-Nami is very kind in general, especially to women and children. In most situations she'll be friendly to other characters.
-She can be very greedy, having a great fascination for treasure and money. Even so she won't compromise her standards for greed.
-She's a bit of a femme fatale, and isn't afraid of using her sex appeal to get what she wants.
-She's very confident in her looks and her sexuality most of the time, but can get embarrassed when she's out of her comfort zone.
-Being more of a woman of science, Nami can be quite skeptical about supernatural things like magic (she'll assume they're explained by Devil Fruits if she sees something like that in other characters)
-She can get scared very easily when it comes to spooky stuff.
-She's into fashion and looking good.

Good targeting topics:
-Adventures, treasure, traveling, especially if they're about specific stuff or anecdotes.
-She loves learning about interesting locations she hasn't visited.
-Her friends.
-Specific questions about weather or navigation knowledge are fine.
-Don't be afraid to be mean to her, or catch her offguard with lines. Anything that gets a strong reaction out of her is usually good.
-Sexual topics are always welcomed.
-Commenting on her outfit is fine, especially if it's something that can get a good reaction out of Nami.

Bad targeting topics:
-"What's that in your belt?" "What's that on your wrist?" She explains both of these things in her generic dialogue. The baton is a weapon that uses the weather to her advantage. The bracelet is basically a compass. Don't ask her what they are. If you want to have a conversation about these items, have your character talk as if they already knew what they are.
-"What does your tattoo mean?" She also explains this in her generic dialogue (marker:tattoo)
-"What is it like being a pirate/navigator?" If you want to ask her about this, make the questions more specific. The more specific the better. Also if you ask her about being a pirate before she takes off her sandals, she'll attempt to deny it, although she might still answer.
-Lines or questions that react to when she drops her poster or when she creates her shower are fine, just know that I usually don't respond to these lines unless they're interesting. (Also, if it's the only thing you target of her, know that you're dead to me.)
